HEADWORD: Silicated
<hw>Sil"i*ca`ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Combined or impregnated with silicon or silica; <as>as,
<ex>silicated</ex> hydrogen; <ex>silicated</ex> rocks</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Silicated soap</b></col>, <cd>a hard soap containing
silicate of soda.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Silicatization</ent>⟦br⟧
